header.description: Property. This message holds a collection of 3d points, plus optional additional information about each point. Time of sensor data acquisition, coordinate frame ID.

points.description: Property. Array of 3d points. Each Point32 should be interpreted as a 3d point in the frame given in the header.

channels.description: Property. Each channel should have the same number of elements as points array, and the data in each channel should correspond 1:1 with each point. Channel names in common practice are listed in ChannelFloat32.msg.
